2
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:05,390
WILL, KEEP THAT SHIRT CLEAN
FOR THE PICNIC, HEAR?

3
00:01:05,430 --> 00:01:08,660
YES, MA'AM.
I WILL.

4
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,400
I MEAN IT!

5
00:01:10,430 --> 00:01:12,430
YEAH, MA,
I PROMISE!

6
00:01:33,820 --> 00:01:35,820
[SIGHS]

7
00:01:50,170 --> 00:01:51,310
[WACK!]

8
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:58,180
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

9
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,300
[WACK!]

10
00:02:24,970 --> 00:02:26,570
[WACK!]

11
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:33,450
[AMBIENT SOUNDS]

12
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:49,260
[WACK!]

13
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,430
WATCH OUT!

14
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:55,400
WILL! YOU JUST RUINED
MARY'S SHOT!!!

15
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,600
OH, QUIT YOUR
WHININ', ROB.

16
00:02:56,640 --> 00:03:00,270
IF I DIDN'T STOP IT, IT WOULDA
ROLLED DOWN TO THE CREEK.

17
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:02,310
STILL SHOULDA
LET IT GO.

18
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:08,850
WELL, IF IT WOULD MAKE
YOU HAPPIER...

19
00:03:19,730 --> 00:03:23,600
EZEKIEL, DEAR, I THINK
EVERYTHING'S READY INSIDE.

20
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:30,800
EVERYBODY,
LET'S GO ON INSIDE.

21
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,840
IT'S TIME FOR
A LITTLE CULTURE.

22
00:03:41,450 --> 00:03:42,950
WELL, GOTTA GO.

23
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:44,550
OH NO,
LITTLE BROTHER.

24
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,950
YOU'RE GETTIN'
THE BALL FIRST,

25
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:49,290
AND IF IT'S IN THE CREEK,
YOU'RE GOIN' IN AFTER IT.

26
00:03:49,330 --> 00:03:51,290
I'M NOT GONNA
GET YOUR BALL.

27
00:03:51,330 --> 00:03:52,830
YOU THREW IT,
YOU FETCH IT...

28
00:03:52,860 --> 00:03:56,430
AND IF NOT,
I'LL TELL PA.

29
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,000
COME ON,
MARY.

30
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:21,860
[SPLASH!]

31
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:32,730
HEY, TOWN BOY.

32
00:04:33,870 --> 00:04:34,870
HEY.

33
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,440
WHAT KINDA
BALL'S THET?

34
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,840
CROQUET.

35
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,450
CROW WHAT?

36
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:48,620
YOU, UH...YOU THROW IT
AT CROWS.

37
00:04:50,990 --> 00:04:52,550
YA LIVE UP THERE?

38
00:04:52,590 --> 00:04:54,090
YEAH.

39
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:56,090
TODAY'S THE SUNDAY
SCHOOL PICNIC.

40
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,960
WHERE DO YOU LIVE?

41
00:04:57,990 --> 00:04:59,690
OVER ON MILL HILL.

42
00:04:59,730 --> 00:05:01,730
I WAS BORN N' BRED
IN A SHOTGUN HOUSE.

43
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:04,830
HEY, SPANGLER,
YOU GOT A GAME TO PLAY

44
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:06,000
WE NEED
THAT BALL!

45
00:05:09,610 --> 00:05:11,340
YOU PLAY BASEBALL?

46
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:14,570
WE'S PLAYIN' A GAME,
IF YOU'D LIKE TO PLAY.

47
00:05:14,610 --> 00:05:16,580
YOU MEAN I CAN
PLAY WITH Y'ALL?

48
00:05:16,610 --> 00:05:18,710
YOU KIN BE
THE UMPIRE.

49
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:19,710
I'M JUST KIDDIN'.

50
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,620
'COURSE YA KIN PLAY.
C'MON.

51
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:46,110
SINCE WE'S A LITTLE
SHORT OF PLAYERS TODAY,

52
00:05:46,140 --> 00:05:48,580
I FOUND US
AN EXTRA.

53
00:05:48,610 --> 00:05:51,980
THIS HERE'S -
WHAT'S YER NAME?

54
00:05:52,010 --> 00:05:52,980
WILL.

55
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:54,580
WILL WRIGHT.

56
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:58,450
WELL, I'M CHICK UH,
THAT'S MY BROTHER PIKE.

57
00:05:58,490 --> 00:06:01,760
AND THET'S WILLIS,
YOU'LL LEARN 'EM.

58
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:05,990
THIS HERE'S
A TOWN BOY.

59
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:07,590
SO?

60
00:06:07,630 --> 00:06:09,960
HE KIN STILL
PLAY BASEBALL.

61
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,830
HEY, TOWN BOY, RECKON
YA KIN SLIDE INTO BASE

62
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:14,570
'THOUT TEARIN'
YER KNICKERS?

63
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,440
[CHUCKLES]

64
00:06:16,470 --> 00:06:19,840
DON'T NO MIND PIKE.
HE'S JUST BEIN' ORN'RY.

65
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,010
[SNIFF, SNIFF]

66
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:30,850
CHICK... I DUNNO
AS I KIN PLAY BALL

67
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:33,120
WITH SOMEBODY THET
SMELLS LIKE SOAP.

68
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:35,020
[CHUCKLES]

69
00:06:38,490 --> 00:06:40,460
YEAH,
THET'S MY BOY.

70
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,160
NOW LET'S
PLAY BALL!

71
00:06:45,630 --> 00:06:49,140
TOWN BOY,
TOWN BOY'S GOT A GLOVE.

72
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:50,700
HAND IT OVER!

73
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:52,840
WILL, WE DON'T
HAVE MANY GLOVES.

74
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:55,010
SO WE LET TH' TEAM IN THE
FIELD USE WHAT WE HAVE.

75
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:57,740
C'MON.

76
00:07:05,890 --> 00:07:10,460
HEY WILL,
YA WANT FIRST UP?

77
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:11,560
C'MON.

78
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,160
SEE WHAT
YOU KIN DO?

79
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:22,470
C'MON WILL,
C'MON WILL.

80
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:25,770
YOU GOT IT...
YOU'LL GET IT.

81
00:07:28,910 --> 00:07:30,510
IT'S OKAY,
YOU'LL GET IT.

82
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:33,010
YOU'LL GET
THE NEXT ONE,

83
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:34,880
JUST MAKE HIM THROW
YOU A GOOD ONE.

84
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:43,020
C'MON WILL.
YOU'LL GET IT.

85
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:50,860
PIKE, WE'RE NOT GOING
TO HAVE THAT TRASH.

86
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:53,600
THET WAS JIST
A WASTE PITCH.

87
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,170
ALL PITCHERS
DO THAT.

88
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,610
YAY, WILL!

89
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,140
(CHEERING)

90
00:08:05,180 --> 00:08:08,920
RUN, RUN, RUN, RUN,
RUN, RUN, RUN!

91
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,020
OH, MAN...!!

92
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:23,000
YAY, WILL!
THET'LL SHOW 'EM!

93
00:08:23,030 --> 00:08:24,900
I RECKON YOU
ARE A BALL PLAYER.

94
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:31,870
OFF WITH YOUR HAT
AS THE FLAG GOES BY!

95
00:08:31,910 --> 00:08:34,740
AND LET THE HEART
HAVE ITS SAY:

96
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:37,880
YOU'RE MAN ENOUGH
FOR THE TEAR IN YOUR EYE

97
00:08:37,910 --> 00:08:40,280
THAT YOU WILL NEVER
WIPE AWAY.

98
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,620
OFF WITH YOUR HAT
AS THE FLAG GOES BY!

99
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:43,620
[WHISPERS]
I DON'T SEE WILL.

100
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:45,150
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE HE IS?

101
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:47,620
AND UNCOVER
THE YOUNGSTER'S HEAD;

102
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:51,290
TEACH HIM TO HOLD IT
HOLY AND HIGH

103
00:08:51,330 --> 00:08:55,060
IN THE SAKE OF
ITS SACRED DEAD.

104
00:08:56,770 --> 00:09:00,030
[CLAPPING]

105
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:11,750
(CHEERING)
YEAH, GO, GO, GO...

106
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:14,050
THET'S OKAY.
WE STILL GOT THE LEAD.

107
00:09:22,190 --> 00:09:25,890
HEY PIKE,
IT'S YER LAST AT BAT.

108
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:27,630
I KNOW IT,
CHICKEN HEAD.

109
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:29,200
JIST SHUT UP
N' PITCH.

110
00:09:41,180 --> 00:09:42,880
PIKE'S UP FIRST THIS
INNING, ISN'T HE?

111
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:43,840
YEAH.

112
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:47,310
TRY PITCHIN' THIS TO HIM
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

113
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:58,190
YOU KNOW, FOR A TOWN BOY YOU
GOT SOME PRETTY GOOD IDEAS.

114
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:21,780
UGH!

115
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,800
LET ME SEE
THAT BALL!

116
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:45,300
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU DID TOWN BOY,

117
00:10:45,340 --> 00:10:48,170
BUT I'LL GIT YOU
FOR THET.

118
00:10:48,210 --> 00:10:49,810
JIST WAIT AN'
SEE IF I DON'T.

119
00:10:58,490 --> 00:11:01,090
ALRIGHT, TWO OUTS TO GO.
WHO'S UP?

120
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:06,190
[VIOLIN MUSIC]

121
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,670
I'M CONCERNED
ABOUT WILL.

122
00:11:19,340 --> 00:11:20,310
ROBERT,

123
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:22,780
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE WILL IS?

124
00:11:22,810 --> 00:11:24,040
LAST TIME I SAW HIM,

125
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:26,310
HE WAS HEADIN' DOWN
THE HILL TOWARD THE CREEK.

126
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:27,450
WHEN WAS THAT?

127
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,680
WHEN YOU
CALLED US IN.

128
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,920
YES, WE'S THE
SLUGGERS TODAY!

129
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:05,190
LET'S GO COOL OFF!

130
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:07,090
YAY!

131
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:18,100
[LAUGHTER, SPLASHING, CHEERS]

132
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:26,970
[LAUGHTER, SPLASHING, CHEERS]

133
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:35,820
[LAUGHTER, SPLASHING, CHEERS]

134
00:12:42,490 --> 00:12:46,360
[LAUGHTER, SPLASHING, CHEERS]

135
00:12:50,830 --> 00:12:52,970
WILL, C'MON,
TAKE A TURN.

136
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:01,210
WILLIAM EDWARD WRIGHT!

137
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:04,340
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

138
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:06,110
GET ON HOME!

139
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:11,050
THE REST OF YOU BOYS,
GET ON HOME, TOO,

140
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:12,190
IF YOU HAVE ONE.

141
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:14,590
WE AIN'T
HURTIN' NOTHIN'.

142
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:17,960
WILLIAM, I'LL MEET
YOU AT THE SHED.

143
00:13:20,230 --> 00:13:22,060
(MOCKING EZEKIEL)
MEET YOU AT THE SHED.

144
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:24,930
HA! SERVES YA RIGHT,
TOWN BOY.

145
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:28,600
YOU AN' YER OL' MAN OUGHT TO
STAY ON YER SIDE O' TH' RIVER.

146
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,500
TOWNIES.

147
00:13:40,380 --> 00:13:46,950
SON...

148
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:48,590
HAVE YOU FORGOTTEN
WHAT YOU'VE BEEN TOLD

149
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:52,190
ABOUT THE BOYS THAT LIVE
ON THAT SIDE OF TOWN?

150
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:54,060
EVER SINCE THE TEXTILE MILL
CAME TO NEWTON

151
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:58,200
THERE'S BEEN AN UNWRITTEN CODE
OF SORTS.

152
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:00,200
WE DON'T INTERFERE
IN THEIR DOINGS

153
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:03,470
AND THEY DON'T
INTERFERE IN OURS.

154
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:06,210
NOW, I'M SURE THERE ARE SOME
FINE FOLKS OVER THERE,

155
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:08,540
BUT WE DON'T MIX
WITH THEM.

156
00:14:08,580 --> 00:14:10,610
SORRY I SNUCK
OFF, PA.

157
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:11,980
BUT WHAT'S WRONG-

158
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:15,110
SORRY YOU DID IT?
OR THAT YOU GOT CAUGHT?

159
00:14:17,650 --> 00:14:19,350
BOTH I GUESS.

160
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:20,350
BUT WHY CAN'T WE-

161
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:21,190
NEVER MIND.

162
00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:24,390
YOU DID WRONG,
AND YOU'LL BE PUNISHED.

163
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,600
STAY PUT.

164
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:31,500
I'M NOT GOING TO SWITCH
YOU OVER THIS.

165
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,610
BUT I DO WANT YOU
TO LEARN A LESSON

166
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:41,440
ABOUT GOING
YOUR OWN WAY.

167
00:14:47,250 --> 00:14:49,280
THERE'LL BE NO BASEBALL
FOR A WEEK!

168
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:51,220
NO BALL?
BUT, PA-

169
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:54,950
NO ARGUMENTS!
THIS IS MY LAST WORD.

170
00:14:54,990 --> 00:14:57,960
IT'S TIME YOU LEARN THAT
YOU CAN'T JUST DO

171
00:14:57,990 --> 00:14:59,360
WHATEVER COMES
TO YOUR MIND.

172
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:00,530
BUT-

173
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:04,530
NO MORE!

174
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:09,470
THERE ARE NO STAINS ON
THE PAGES OF TOMORROW.

175
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:17,310
AND NO BASEBALL NEITHER.

176
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:34,990
HEY, TOWN BOY!

177
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,100
WHACHA DOIN'
UP HERE?

178
00:15:39,130 --> 00:15:41,700
I WANNA SEE IF YE KIN
COME PLAY BASEBALL AGIN.

179
00:15:41,740 --> 00:15:44,500
NOT ALLOWED TO -
FOR A WEEK.

180
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:46,370
CAIN'T YA JIST
LIKE SNEAK OFF?

181
00:15:46,410 --> 00:15:48,110
TELL 'EM YER GOIN' FISHIN'
OR SOMETHIN'?

182
00:15:48,140 --> 00:15:49,180
THET'S WHAT
I DO.

183
00:15:49,210 --> 00:15:52,350
I DON'T WANT TO GET IN
WORSE TROUBLE WITH MY PA.

184
00:15:52,380 --> 00:15:53,610
HOW ABOUT SATURDAY?

185
00:15:53,650 --> 00:15:55,420
CAN YOU
COME SATURDAY?

186
00:15:55,450 --> 00:15:58,080
YEAH, SATURDAY
WILL BE A WEEK.

187
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,520
ALRIGHT, I'LL MEET
YOU AT THE TRESTLE.

188
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:14,630
(MOM CALLING OUT)
WILL!

189
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:18,240
RISE AND SHINE!

190
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:20,710
HONEY,
YOU KNOW IT'S SATURDAY?

191
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:24,680
DON'T WAIT
DINNER ON ME, MA!

192
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:54,510
HEY, TOWN BOY.

193
00:16:54,540 --> 00:16:55,770
YOU READY TO PLAY
SOME BASEBALL?

194
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:57,280
SURE!

195
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:07,120
CAN I CARRY
YOUR GLOVE?

196
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,450
OKAY.

197
00:17:32,150 --> 00:17:32,810
[WACK!]

198
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,120
DO WE GET TO PLAY
ON THIS FIELD?

199
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,790
SINCE THE MILL WORKERS
WORK UNTIL NOON,

200
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,790
WE CAN PLAY IN
THE MORNING.

201
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:49,330
WHAT DO YOU HAVE TO DO
TO GET ON THE MILL TEAM?

202
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,700
FIRST, YOU GOTTA WORK
FOR THE MILL.

203
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:53,400
THEN, I'VE
GOT TIME.

204
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,830
FER WHAT?

205
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:58,770
FOR THAT.

206
00:17:58,810 --> 00:18:00,420
THAT'S WHAT.

207
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,260
[WACK!]

208
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,800
[WACK!]

209
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,550
[WACK!]

210
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:29,720
C'MON CHICK, YOU'RE HANDIN' IT
TO HIM ON A SILVER PLATTER.

211
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:32,720
BE QUIET PIKE, I'M GIVIN'
HIM MY GOOD STUFF.

212
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:34,420
YOU READY, WILL?

213
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,600
[WACK!]

214
00:18:41,930 --> 00:18:42,870
DON'T LET 'IM
FOOL YA, SCOOP.

215
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:46,240
HE'S BEEN HITTIN' MY
BROTHER'S STUFF FER YEARS.

216
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:48,370
YOU THINK YOU KIN
DO ANY BETTER?

217
00:18:48,410 --> 00:18:49,540
WATCH ME.

218
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:51,840
(SCOOP)
OKAY, CHICK.

219
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:54,210
LET'S SEE WHAT HE CAN DO
WITH SOMEBODY ELSE.

220
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,830
[WACK!]

221
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:24,570
[WACK!]

222
00:19:55,470 --> 00:19:56,740
[WACK!]

223
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:06,620
OKAY,
BRING IT ON IN.

224
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:23,570
WILL WRIGHT,
HUH.

225
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,400
OKAY, I'LL GIVE
YOU A CHANCE.

226
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:28,940
BUT YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO PROVE
YOURSELF IN THE REAL GAMES.

227
00:20:28,970 --> 00:20:31,610
FIRST, I NEED YOU TO GO TO THE
MILL AND SIGN UP FOR WORK.

228
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:35,810
PRACTICE AFTER WORK, GAMES
ARE ON SATURDAY AFTERNOONS.

229
00:20:35,850 --> 00:20:36,810
WHAT DO YA SAY?

230
00:20:36,850 --> 00:20:39,550
DO BASEBALL SCOUTS COME DOWN
TO WATCH MILL GAMES?

231
00:20:39,580 --> 00:20:41,020
YOU'RE ONE OF
THOSE, HUH?

232
00:20:41,050 --> 00:20:42,420
FIGURES.

233
00:20:42,450 --> 00:20:43,920
YEAH, YOU MAKE
ENOUGH NOISE.

234
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:46,260
SCOUTS'LL COME DOWN FROM
CHARLOTTE LOOKIN' FOR NEW BLOOD.

235
00:20:46,290 --> 00:20:49,260
BUT YER GONNA HAVE TO
PROVE YOURSELF FIRST.

236
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:50,930
ARE YA IN?

237
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:53,430
YES, SIR.
I AM.

238
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,730
POLITE, I LIKE THAT.

239
00:20:55,770 --> 00:20:58,530
SHOW UP AT THE MILL
GATE MONDAY MORNIN'.

240
00:20:58,570 --> 00:21:01,270
CHICK'LL SHOW YOU
WHERE TO GO.

241
00:21:01,310 --> 00:21:02,300
NOW WE'RE TALKIN'.

242
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:03,840
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF HIM.

243
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:06,010
