469
00:38:24,780 --> 00:38:26,410
PLEASED TO MEET YA.

470
00:38:26,450 --> 00:38:27,480
I'M YER FLOOR BOSS.

471
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:30,950
BUT I'M GONNA LET CHICK
HERE SHOW YOU AROUND TODAY.

472
00:38:30,990 --> 00:38:33,720
HEAR YOU CAN HIT
A BASEBALL A LONG WAY.

473
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:34,820
I RECKON.

474
00:38:34,860 --> 00:38:36,320
WELL, WE'RE GLAD
TO HAVE YA.

475
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:38,690
MAYBE WE CAN BEAT THAT
ANDERSON TEAM THIS YEAR.

476
00:38:38,730 --> 00:38:40,330
CERTAINLY HOPE SO.

477
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:52,440
[AMBIENT MACHINE SOUNDS]

478
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:28,010
HERE'S YOUR WRENCH
AND YOUR SCREW DRIVER.

479
00:39:30,850 --> 00:39:32,450
WHAT DO I DO
WITH 'EM?

480
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:37,620
CRANK BOLTS AND
TURN SCREWS, IDIOT!

481
00:39:39,490 --> 00:39:41,720
IGNORE HIM.

482
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:43,560
YOU'RE A "O"FFICIAL
MECHANIC NOW.

483
00:39:43,590 --> 00:39:45,490
SO IF SOMEONE HOLLERS
THEIR MACHINE IS STUCK,

484
00:39:45,530 --> 00:39:46,960
YOU JIST GO FIX IT.

485
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:48,860
BUT I DON'T
KNOW ABOUT-

486
00:39:48,900 --> 00:39:51,170
YOU DON'T NEED
TO KNOW NOTHING.

487
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:53,500
YOU JIST CHECK ALL THE NUTS
AND BOLTS ON THE STUCK LOOM

488
00:39:53,540 --> 00:39:54,500
AND IF'N THEY'S ALL TIGHT,

489
00:39:54,540 --> 00:39:56,840
THEN YOU GO GIT
A REAL MECHANIC.

490
00:39:56,870 --> 00:39:58,670
SIT DOWN.

491
00:40:02,780 --> 00:40:04,050
I'M GONNA TEACH YA HOW
TA MAKE A LITTLE EXTRA MONEY

492
00:40:04,080 --> 00:40:05,810
WITH A DECK OF CARDS.

493
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:11,950
YOU SURE THIS IS
AN HONEST DAY'S WORK?

494
00:40:11,990 --> 00:40:14,060
YOU'RE TOO GREEN TO SPIT,
TOWN BOY.

495
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:18,860
[AMBIENT MACHINE SOUNDS]

496
00:40:50,490 --> 00:40:52,860
OH! I'M SORRY.
I - DIDN'T SEE YOU THERE.

497
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:56,830
I SAW YOU - AT THE
TRYOUTS THE OTHER DAY.

498
00:40:56,870 --> 00:40:57,870
OH?

499
00:40:57,900 --> 00:40:58,900
I'M NEW HERE.

500
00:40:58,940 --> 00:41:00,130
I JUST SIGNED ON
TO PLAY BALL.

501
00:41:00,170 --> 00:41:01,240
SO I GATHERED.

502
00:41:01,270 --> 00:41:03,140
DO YOU WORK
AT THE MILL?

503
00:41:03,170 --> 00:41:05,910
IN THE OFFICE.
I'M A SECRETARY.

504
00:41:08,510 --> 00:41:10,110
YOU LIKE MUSIC?

505
00:41:10,150 --> 00:41:13,250
I THINK IT'S ONE OF GOD'S
GREATEST GIFTS TO US.

506
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:15,580
MY MOM MADE ME TAKE PIANO
WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.

507
00:41:15,620 --> 00:41:16,890
YOU PLAY?

508
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:19,720
I HAVEN'T KEPT UP
WITH IT.

509
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:22,260
TOO BAD.

510
00:41:22,290 --> 00:41:25,530
SAY, I HAVEN'T
INTRODUCED MYSELF.

511
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:26,590
WILL WRIGHT.

512
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:27,930
GINNIE.

513
00:41:33,700 --> 00:41:37,140
AND ACTUALLY, I WAS JUST
TALKIN' TO MY FRIEND CHICK

514
00:41:37,170 --> 00:41:39,110
THAT WE SHOULD FIND
SOMETHING TO DO AFTER WORK.

515
00:41:39,140 --> 00:41:41,580
AND HERE'S
THIS CONCERT!

516
00:41:41,610 --> 00:41:42,780
SO YOU'LL COME?

517
00:41:42,810 --> 00:41:44,780
COURSE WE'LL BE THERE!

518
00:41:44,810 --> 00:41:46,150
GOOD.

519
00:41:55,630 --> 00:41:58,590
OH, YOU'VE
DONE IT NOW.

520
00:41:58,630 --> 00:42:00,260
PIKE'S SWEET
ON THET GIRL.

521
00:42:00,300 --> 00:42:02,530
YEA, BUT IS SHE
SWEET ON HIM?

522
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:12,640
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

523
00:42:20,820 --> 00:42:22,050
HI WILL!

524
00:42:22,090 --> 00:42:23,280
HEY, BO.

525
00:42:25,620 --> 00:42:26,720
YOU BEEN PRACTICING
YOUR BASEBALL SKILLS?

526
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:27,590
YEAH!

527
00:42:27,620 --> 00:42:28,390
YEAH?

528
00:42:28,430 --> 00:42:29,760
ALRIGHT, WHY DON'T
YOU COME WITH US.

529
00:42:34,630 --> 00:42:38,630
[RAGTIME PIANO MUSIC]

530
00:43:10,300 --> 00:43:19,270
[CHEERING]

531
00:43:19,310 --> 00:43:22,180
HEY ROOKIE,
SHOW US WHACHA GOT.

532
00:43:22,210 --> 00:43:23,280
GIVE US ONE OF THEM
LONG BALLS, HUH?

533
00:43:23,310 --> 00:43:24,650
YES SIR.

534
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:26,980
[CHEERING]

535
00:43:27,020 --> 00:43:28,880
HIT THAT BALL.
YOU CAN DO IT.

536
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:30,020
C'MON WILL.

537
00:43:30,050 --> 00:43:31,290
HIT IT OUTTA HERE.

538
00:43:31,320 --> 00:43:33,050
(UMPIRE) STRIKE ONE.

539
00:43:33,090 --> 00:43:35,290
(CROWD) THAT'S OKAY.
C'MON, YOU CAN DO IT.

540
00:43:35,330 --> 00:43:38,160
YOU'LL GET THE NEXT ONE.

541
00:43:38,190 --> 00:43:39,990
(SCOOP) LET'S HAVE SOME
PEP OUT THERE.

542
00:43:40,030 --> 00:43:41,900
STRIKE TWO.

543
00:43:43,900 --> 00:43:45,170
(CROWD) C'MON MAKE 'EM
PITCH TO YOU.

544
00:43:46,440 --> 00:43:48,400
STRIKE THREE,
YOU'RE OUT.

545
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:50,870
(CROWD)
YOU'LL GET THE NEXT ONE.

546
00:43:50,910 --> 00:43:53,910
[CHEERING]

547
00:44:02,050 --> 00:44:03,420
(SCOOP)
LET'S GO BOYS.

548
00:44:03,450 --> 00:44:05,890
COME ON, LET'S SEE
SOME PEP OUT THERE.

549
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:07,990
YOU'RE LIKE A BUNCH
OF DEAD FISH.

550
00:44:12,100 --> 00:44:14,060
SPANGLER, YOU KNOW
WHAT I TOLD YA.

551
00:44:18,070 --> 00:44:20,730
STRIKE ONE.

552
00:44:20,770 --> 00:44:23,770
[CHEERING]

553
00:44:23,810 --> 00:44:25,410
[WACK!]

554
00:44:25,440 --> 00:44:30,110
[CHEERING]

555
00:44:32,050 --> 00:44:37,250
UHHH, WHAT ARE YA THINKIN'?
UGH!

556
00:44:40,820 --> 00:44:42,360
YOU KNOW
WHAT I THINK?

557
00:44:42,390 --> 00:44:45,890
I THINK THAT WAS THE WORST
FIRST GAME I EVER SAW!

558
00:44:45,930 --> 00:44:47,900
AIN'T GONNA HAPPEN
NO MORE! YA HEAR?

559
00:44:47,930 --> 00:44:51,770
MAYBE WE GOT A BAD LUCK CHARM
SPLITTIN' TH' TEAM UP, SCOOP.

560
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:55,170
SPANGLER, YOU WORRY ABOUT
YOUR OWN SORRY GAME

561
00:44:55,210 --> 00:44:58,170
N' KEEP YOUR
TRAP SHUT.

562
00:44:58,210 --> 00:45:01,440
ALL OF YA BAD
LUCK TODAY.

563
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:03,110
CLEAR ON OUT.

564
00:45:11,390 --> 00:45:12,390
[THUD!]

565
00:45:14,460 --> 00:45:18,230
I RECKON YOU GOIN' TO BE
JOININ' US FER A DRINK?

566
00:45:18,260 --> 00:45:21,030
I DON'T
GUESS I AM.

567
00:45:21,060 --> 00:45:23,760
MAYBE YOU ALL COULD TAKE
A LESSON FROM THE ROOKIE

568
00:45:23,800 --> 00:45:26,930
AND SPEND SOME TIME THINKIN'
'BOUT WHAT JUST HAPPENED.

569
00:45:26,970 --> 00:45:29,270
HE'S GOT A LOT MORE T' THINK
ABOUT THAN THE REST OF US.

570
00:45:35,490 --> 00:45:36,990
[WACK!]

571
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:46,170
[WACK!]

572
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:48,840
YOU GOT THE MAKIN'S
OF A NATURAL HITTER.

573
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:51,910
VERY FUNNY.

574
00:45:51,950 --> 00:45:54,050
WHO ARE YOU?

575
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:55,950
JUST A FAN.

576
00:45:55,980 --> 00:45:57,950
CAN I SHOW
YOU SOMETHIN'?

577
00:46:01,090 --> 00:46:03,320
I'VE WATCHED EVERY BIG STICK
COME THROUGH HERE -

578
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:05,920
FROM SHOELESS JOE JACKSON
ALL THE WAY DOWN.

579
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:09,190
AND THEY ALL HAVE
ONE LITTLE SECRET.

580
00:46:09,230 --> 00:46:12,200
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE
GONNA TELL ME.

581
00:46:12,230 --> 00:46:14,970
IT'S ALL ABOUT
A LEVEL SWING.

582
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:17,230
RIGHT NOW YOU'RE SWINGIN'
UP AT THE BALL.

583
00:46:17,270 --> 00:46:19,470
YOU'VE GOTTA LEVEL OUT SO
WHEN YOU STRIKE THE BALL

584
00:46:19,510 --> 00:46:22,140
IT'S LIKE A HAMMER
HITTIN' A NAIL.

585
00:46:22,170 --> 00:46:24,880
AND THIS IS
THE HAMMER.

586
00:46:24,910 --> 00:46:28,310
MADE IT MYSELF.

587
00:46:28,350 --> 00:46:30,450
IT'S THE BEST BATTING
COACH I'VE SEEN.

588
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:32,250
C'MON.

589
00:46:43,860 --> 00:46:46,500
TAKES A LITTLE BIT
OF PRACTICE BUT...

590
00:46:47,900 --> 00:46:48,570
[WACK!]

591
00:46:51,900 --> 00:46:53,970
IT'LL FLATTEN OUT
YOUR SWING.

592
00:46:54,010 --> 00:46:56,870
AND THE WEIGHT'LL
INCREASE YOUR BAT SPEED.

593
00:46:56,910 --> 00:46:58,380
I NEED SOMETHIN'.

594
00:47:01,250 --> 00:47:03,110
GIVE
IT A TRY.

595
00:47:16,100 --> 00:47:17,260
[WACK!]

596
00:47:19,100 --> 00:47:21,600
LIKE I SAID, TAKES
A LITTLE BIT A' PRACTICE.

597
00:47:21,630 --> 00:47:23,400
I CAN SEE.

598
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:25,900
YOU GOT ANY GOOD IDEAS
FOR READING A CURVE BALL?

599
00:47:30,140 --> 00:47:33,080
NEVER SWING AT A PITCH
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN.

600
00:47:33,110 --> 00:47:35,280
WATCH HIS RELEASE UNTIL
YOU KNOW WHAT HE'S THROWIN'

601
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:37,210
AS HE LETS IT GO.

602
00:47:37,250 --> 00:47:41,220
AND JIST GOTTA HANG BACK AND
WAIT 'TIL IT DROPS INTO ZONE.

603
00:47:41,250 --> 00:47:45,160
EASY TO SAY,
NOT QUITE SO EASY TO DO.

604
00:47:45,190 --> 00:47:47,290
YOU GOT AN ANSWER
FOR EVERYTHING.

605
00:47:47,330 --> 00:47:49,660
BEEN AROUND A WHILE.

606
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:52,400
KEEP THE HAMMER
AS LONG AS YOU LIKE.

607
00:47:52,430 --> 00:47:54,970
HERE'S YOUR
BUCKET OF NAILS.

608
00:48:03,240 --> 00:48:04,310
[WACK!]

609
00:48:06,110 --> 00:48:07,140
[SIGHS]

610
00:48:19,530 --> 00:48:20,990
[WACK!]

611
00:48:41,280 --> 00:48:42,250
[WACK!]

612
00:49:03,670 --> 00:49:13,710
[CHURCH BELL RINGING]

613
00:49:13,710 --> 00:49:36,030
[CHURCH BELL RINGING]

614
00:49:46,080 --> 00:49:48,650
I DON'T REALLY HAVE
TO TAKE A BATH, DO I?

615
00:49:48,680 --> 00:49:51,550
YOU SAID
YOU WOULD.

616
00:49:56,320 --> 00:49:59,220
YOU AGREED TO PAY ME
TWO BITS TO COME.

617
00:49:59,260 --> 00:50:01,560
BATH'S EXTRA.

618
00:50:01,590 --> 00:50:06,500
I'LL GIVE YOU FOUR BITS
JUST TO BATHE AND COME ON.

619
00:50:06,530 --> 00:50:08,530
UP FRONT.

620
00:50:19,150 --> 00:50:22,280
ONE OF OUR FAVORITES,
BICYCLE BUILT FOR TWO.

621
00:50:24,320 --> 00:50:28,320
[BAND PLAYS]

622
00:51:12,570 --> 00:51:24,280
(CLAPPING)

623
00:51:24,310 --> 00:51:27,140
JOHN PHILLIP SOUSA'S,
KING COTTON.

624
00:51:30,550 --> 00:51:33,550
[BAND PLAYS]

625
00:51:54,710 --> 00:51:59,810
[PIANO MUSIC]

626
00:51:59,850 --> 00:52:03,810
IT'S THE FIRST GOOD RAIN
WE'VE HAD IN A WHILE.

627
00:52:03,850 --> 00:52:05,720
YEP.

628
00:52:05,750 --> 00:52:09,290
WE CAME TO NEWTON FROM A MILL IN
CHATTANOOGA YEAR BEFORE LAST.

629
00:52:09,820 --> 00:52:11,720
DID YOU
GROW UP HERE?

630
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:14,260
YEAH, OVER ON
THE TOWN SIDE.

631
00:52:14,290 --> 00:52:15,660
IT'S A PRETTY
LITTLE PLACE.

632
00:52:15,690 --> 00:52:17,390
IT IS.

633
00:52:17,430 --> 00:52:19,160
I WON'T BE HERE FOR LONG
IF I CAN JUST CATCH THE EYE

634
00:52:19,200 --> 00:52:23,530
OF THE CHARLOTTE
SPINNERS SCOUT.

635
00:52:23,570 --> 00:52:26,840
SAY, HOW DO YOU PLAY AND
TALK AT THE SAME TIME?

636
00:52:29,580 --> 00:52:31,540
WELL, YOU GET USED TO IT
AFTER A WHILE.

637
00:52:31,580 --> 00:52:32,740
SOMEONE'S ALWAYS TALKING
IN THIS EAR

638
00:52:32,780 --> 00:52:34,310
WHILE I'M TRYING
TO LISTEN WITH THE OTHER

639
00:52:34,350 --> 00:52:36,710
WHEN I PLAY THE PIANO
FOR THE MILL CHURCH.

640
00:52:36,750 --> 00:52:37,550
HAVE YOU BEEN?

641
00:52:37,580 --> 00:52:40,320
NO, NOT YET.

642
00:52:40,350 --> 00:52:41,850
I'M SURE I WILL.

643
00:52:41,890 --> 00:52:43,420
WHY DON'T YOU PLAY
SOMETHING FOR ME.

644
00:52:43,460 --> 00:52:46,460
NO, NO, LIKE I SAID
IT'S BEEN YEARS.

645
00:52:46,490 --> 00:52:48,660
NOW I CAN TELL YOU
HAVE NICE HANDS -

646
00:52:48,690 --> 00:52:51,460
FOR PLAYIN' THE PIANO
AND FOR PLAYIN' BASEBALL.

647
00:52:51,500 --> 00:52:55,470
NO, IT WOULD NOT
BE A GOOD IDEA.

648
00:52:55,500 --> 00:52:58,540
DO YOU LIKE
BASEBALL?

649
00:52:58,570 --> 00:53:00,600
NOT MUCH.

650
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:03,740
BUT DADDY WILL
NEVER MISS A GAME.

651
00:53:03,780 --> 00:53:05,280
SO YOU THINK YOU
COULD COME WATCH US

652
00:53:05,310 --> 00:53:07,680
AT THE ANDERSON GAME
THIS WEEK?

653
00:53:07,710 --> 00:53:12,420
I WILL - IF YOU'LL COME
TO VISIT AT OUR CHURCH.

654
00:53:12,450 --> 00:53:15,950
YOU COULD BRING IMOGENE ALONG
TO KEEP CHICK COMPANY.

655
00:53:15,990 --> 00:53:18,420
TIME TO GIT GOIN',
HUH WILL?

656
00:53:18,460 --> 00:53:21,430
YEAH, I
RECKON.

657
00:53:21,460 --> 00:53:23,260
SO, WE'LL SEE
YOU SATURDAY!

658
00:53:23,300 --> 00:53:24,960
OKAY.

659
00:53:33,440 --> 00:53:34,800
(RADIO ANNOUNCER) WELL, LADIES
AND GENTLEMEN,

660
00:53:34,840 --> 00:53:37,410
THIS HAS BEEN A
HARD FOUGHT GAME.

661
00:53:37,440 --> 00:53:39,840
HERE WE ARE IN THE TOP
OF THE NINTH INNING

662
00:53:39,880 --> 00:53:43,550
AND THE SCORE IS STILL TIED
AT ONE RUN APIECE.

663
00:53:43,580 --> 00:53:46,280
SLOAN IS STILL ON THE MOUND
FOR ANDERSON.

664
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:48,850
HE'S PITCHED
A GREAT GAME TODAY.

665
00:53:48,890 --> 00:53:52,320
AND NOW THE STRONG HORSE
OF THE NEWTON TEAM,

666
00:53:52,360 --> 00:53:55,630
THEIR RETURNING HERO,
APPROACHES THE PLATE.

667
00:53:55,660 --> 00:53:59,560
PIKE SPANGLER IS NEWTON'S
POWER MAN IN THE BATTER'S BOX.

668
00:53:59,600 --> 00:54:01,570
SLOAN IS READY NOW.

669
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:03,930
THERE'S A WIND UP
AND THE PITCH...

670
00:54:03,970 --> 00:54:05,470
STRIKE.

671
00:54:05,500 --> 00:54:07,570
STRIKE ONE ON SPANGLER.

672
00:54:12,980 --> 00:54:14,480
BALL.

673
00:54:14,510 --> 00:54:16,280
ONE AND ONE
THE COUNT

674
00:54:16,320 --> 00:54:18,820
AS SPANGLER STEPS
BACK UP TO THE PLATE.

675
00:54:18,850 --> 00:54:21,490
HIS KID BROTHER CHICK,
NEWTON'S STARTING PITCHER,

676
00:54:21,520 --> 00:54:23,790
SCORED THE TEAM'S
ONLY RUN.

677
00:54:25,590 --> 00:54:27,560
HERE'S THE NEXT PITCH.

678
00:54:27,590 --> 00:54:28,430
HE SWINGS...

679
00:54:28,460 --> 00:54:30,890
IT'S A HIGH POP UP
GOING FOR A LEFT.

680
00:54:30,930 --> 00:54:33,830
LOOKS LIKE THIS ONE
MAY BE DRIFTING FOUL.

681
00:54:33,870 --> 00:54:36,770
FRAZIER'S TRYING TO CHASE
IT DOWN FOR THE OUT.

682
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:38,600
AND FRAZIER HAS IT.

683
00:54:38,640 --> 00:54:40,470
TWO OUTS.

684
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:42,770
NEWTON'S DOWN
TO THEIR LAST OUT.

685
00:54:42,810 --> 00:54:47,540
LOOKS LIKE PIKE SPANGLER IS
A RUN-OF-THE-MILL HITTER TODAY.

686
00:54:47,580 --> 00:54:49,580
NEWTON NOW LOOKS FOR RELIEF

687
00:54:49,620 --> 00:54:51,680
FROM THEIR ROOKIE
RIGHT FIELDER,

688
00:54:51,720 --> 00:54:52,950
WILL WRIGHT.

689
00:54:52,980 --> 00:54:55,950
WILL HAILS FROM THE
UP-TOWN SIDE OF NEWTON,

690
00:54:55,990 --> 00:54:59,420
AND THIS IS HIS FIRST
YEAR OF ORGANIZED BALL.

691
00:54:59,460 --> 00:55:03,730
WRIGHT MAY BE NEWTON'S
LAST CHANCE FOR A WIN.

692
00:55:06,600 --> 00:55:09,700
NOW HE'S AT THE PLATE...

693
00:55:09,740 --> 00:55:12,340
THERE'S THE WINDUP
AND THE PITCH.

694
00:55:12,370 --> 00:55:13,970
STRIKE.

695
00:55:14,010 --> 00:55:15,610
IT'S A STRIKE.

696
00:55:15,640 --> 00:55:18,840
THAT WAS A SWEET ONE BUT
THE NEWCOMER PASSED IT UP.

697
00:55:18,880 --> 00:55:21,480
0 AND 1 THE COUNT.

698
00:55:21,510 --> 00:55:25,050
NEXT PITCH IS A BREAKING BALL:
HIGH AND OUTSIDE.

699
00:55:25,080 --> 00:55:26,950
ONE AND ONE
THE COUNT.

700
00:55:30,860 --> 00:55:32,020
STRIKE.

701
00:55:32,060 --> 00:55:34,730
WRIGHT SCANS
THE STANDS.

702
00:55:34,760 --> 00:55:38,430
MAYBE HE'S LOOKING
FOR INSPIRATION.

703
00:55:38,460 --> 00:55:39,860
ONE AND TWO
THE COUNT.

704
00:55:49,910 --> 00:55:50,710
THERE'S THE PITCH-

705
00:55:50,740 --> 00:55:52,910
[WACK!]

706
00:55:52,940 --> 00:55:56,750
IT'S A LONG LINE DRIVE
WAY OUT TO CENTER FIELD.

707
00:55:56,780 --> 00:55:58,750
THE CENTER FIELDER'S
BACK TO THE TREES.

708
00:55:58,780 --> 00:56:00,780
IT'S GONE!

709
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:03,720
[CHEERING]

710
00:56:03,760 --> 00:56:07,020
A LONG HOME RUN
FOR WILL WRIGHT.

711
00:56:07,060 --> 00:56:09,730
NEWTON TAKES THE LEAD,
TWO TO ONE,

712
00:56:09,760 --> 00:56:13,960
AND WILL WRIGHT HAS TIPPED
THE SCALES FOR HIS TEAM.

713
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:17,100
WHAT A GAME FOR
IRON WILL WRIGHT,

714
00:56:17,140 --> 00:56:19,870
THE NEXT BIG STICK
AT NEWTON.

715
00:56:21,870 --> 00:56:24,440
THERE'S THE WINDUP
AND THE PITCH,

716
00:56:24,480 --> 00:56:26,840
AND THAT'S
STRIKE THREE.

717
00:56:26,880 --> 00:56:28,950
THAT'S THE LAST
OUT FOR NEWTON.

718
00:56:33,150 --> 00:56:34,850
WE GO TO THE BOTTOM
OF THE NINTH.

719
00:56:34,890 --> 00:56:38,490
WITH NEWTON AHEAD ON
WRIGHT'S LONG HOME RUN.

720
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:40,990
NOW IT'S UP TO YOUNG
CHICK SPANGLER

721
00:56:41,030 --> 00:56:45,060
TO SEE IF HE CAN HOLD THE LEAD
FOR THREE MORE OUTS.

722
00:56:45,100 --> 00:56:49,770
[CHEERING]

723
00:56:54,810 --> 00:56:56,040
HE'S OUT!

724
00:56:56,070 --> 00:56:57,970
THAT'S ONE DOWN,

725
00:56:58,010 --> 00:57:02,510
THAT LONG HOME RUN IS LOOKING
BETTER AND BETTER FOR NEWTON.

726
00:57:08,650 --> 00:57:09,650
STRIKE THREE.

727
00:57:09,690 --> 00:57:11,490
AND THAT'S TWO DOWN.

728
00:57:11,520 --> 00:57:13,990
ANDERSON'S DOWN
TO THEIR LAST OUT.

729
00:57:14,030 --> 00:57:22,930
[CHEERING]

730
00:57:28,510 --> 00:57:29,670
BALL.

731
00:57:38,180 --> 00:57:44,820
[CHEERING]

732
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:48,830
[WACK!]

733
00:57:48,860 --> 00:57:52,000
IT'S A LONG FLY BALL,
ITS WAY OUT TO CENTER FIELD.

734
00:57:52,030 --> 00:57:53,230
THIS ONE'S DEEP.

735
00:57:53,260 --> 00:57:58,000
WRIGHT'S GOING BACK, BACK, HE'S
AT THE TREES, AND HE'S GOT IT.

736
00:57:58,040 --> 00:58:03,040
NEWTON WINS, NEWTON WINS,
NEWTON WINS!

737
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:25,960
[TRUCK ENGINE]

738
00:58:45,780 --> 00:58:47,920
C'MON, WILL,
SHE AIN'T HERE.

739
00:58:47,950 --> 00:58:50,620
AN' I FER ONE DON'T WANT TO BE
HERE WHEN TH' SUN GOES DOWN.

740
00:58:50,660 --> 00:58:51,150
