FOLLOW YOU INTO.

940
01:13:52,760 --> 01:13:54,590
IMOGENE, WE CAN COME
INTO TOWN ANOTHER DAY.

941
01:13:54,630 --> 01:13:56,460
LET'S GO.

942
01:13:56,490 --> 01:13:59,500
WAIT, GINNIE.
WAIT A MINUTE, GINNIE.

943
01:13:59,530 --> 01:14:00,600
WAIT A MINUTE.

944
01:14:00,630 --> 01:14:02,800
DON'T FOLLOW ME.

945
01:14:02,830 --> 01:14:05,470
LOOK, I KNOW HOW THINGS LOOKED
AT THE GAME THE OTHER DAY.

946
01:14:05,500 --> 01:14:07,870
I THOUGHT YOU
WERE A CHRISTIAN.

947
01:14:07,910 --> 01:14:09,670
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
BY THAT?

948
01:14:09,710 --> 01:14:11,610
WERE YOU DRUNK?

949
01:14:11,640 --> 01:14:14,510
GINNIE, LISTEN.

950
01:14:14,550 --> 01:14:17,610
I PROMISED MA BEFORE I LEFT THAT
I WOULDN'T EVEN TOUCH A DROP.

951
01:14:17,650 --> 01:14:18,980
WHAT YOU SAW AT THE GAME
THE OTHER DAY -

952
01:14:19,020 --> 01:14:21,120
THAT WAS JUST
THE TEAM DRINKING.

953
01:14:21,150 --> 01:14:22,520
WELL, IT LOOKED LIKE YOU
WERE GOING RIGHT ALONG

954
01:14:22,550 --> 01:14:24,850
WITH THE REST OF THEM.

955
01:14:24,890 --> 01:14:27,790
YEAH, I KNOW, THEY DO KINDA
GIVE ME A HARD TIME ABOUT IT.

956
01:14:27,830 --> 01:14:29,860
YOU'RE SURE WE CAN'T
GIVE YOU A RIDE NOW?

957
01:14:29,890 --> 01:14:31,630
THANKS FOR THE OFFER
BUT WE'LL WALK.

958
01:14:31,660 --> 01:14:33,030
LET'S GO.

959
01:14:44,780 --> 01:14:47,210
CHICK, LOOKS LIKE I'M
BACK ON THE WATER WAGON.

960
01:14:47,240 --> 01:14:48,880
WHAT?

961
01:14:48,910 --> 01:14:51,280
WHY?
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

962
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:53,520
NEVER MIND.

963
01:14:57,020 --> 01:14:59,590
BUT I'M DONE
DRINKIN' FOR GOOD.

964
01:14:59,620 --> 01:15:01,490
I MADE UP MY MIND.

965
01:15:14,760 --> 01:15:18,760
[CAR ENGINE AND MUSIC]

966
01:15:48,620 --> 01:15:50,720
I KNOW OF A WORLD THAT
IS SUNK IN SHAME,

967
01:15:50,760 --> 01:15:52,790
WHERE HEARTS ARE
FAINT AND TIRE,

968
01:15:52,830 --> 01:15:54,630
BUT I KNOW OF A NAME,
A PRECIOUS NAME,

969
01:15:54,660 --> 01:15:56,860
THAT CAN SET
THAT WORLD ON FIRE.

970
01:15:56,900 --> 01:15:59,670
IT'S JESUS CHRIST,
THE SON OF GOD.

971
01:15:59,700 --> 01:16:02,200
THIRTY-TWO YEARS AGO I WALKED
DOWN A STREET IN CHICAGO IN

972
01:16:02,240 --> 01:16:05,170
COMPANY WITH SOME BALL PLAYERS
WHO WERE FAMOUS IN THIS WORLD.

973
01:16:05,210 --> 01:16:06,740
SOME OF THEM
ARE DEAD NOW.

974
01:16:06,770 --> 01:16:07,970
IT WAS SUNDAY AFTERNOON.

975
01:16:08,010 --> 01:16:10,310
AND WE GOT TANKED UP AND WENT
DOWN AND SAT ON A STREET CORNER.

976
01:16:10,350 --> 01:16:13,880
SAY, I NEVER GO BY THAT PLACE,
BUT I THANK GOD FOR SAVING ME.

977
01:16:13,910 --> 01:16:16,280
IT'S VAN BUREN STREET,
CHICAGO.

978
01:16:16,320 --> 01:16:18,650
WELL, AS I SAY, WE SAT DOWN ON
A CORNER AND ACROSS THE STREET,

979
01:16:18,690 --> 01:16:21,190
A COMPANY OF MEN AND WOMEN
WERE PLAYING ON INSTRUMENTS

980
01:16:21,220 --> 01:16:24,320
AND SINGING THE OLD GOSPEL SONGS
I USED TO HEAR MY MOTHER SING

981
01:16:24,360 --> 01:16:26,730
BACK IN THE LOG CABIN
IN AMES, IOWA

982
01:16:26,760 --> 01:16:29,160
AND BACK IN THE CHURCH WHERE
I USED TO GO TO SUNDAY SCHOOL.

983
01:16:29,200 --> 01:16:32,870
AND GOD PAINTED ON THE CANVAS
OF MY MEMORY A VIVID PICTURE

984
01:16:32,900 --> 01:16:35,130
OF THE SCENES OF OTHER
DAYS AND OTHER FACES-

985
01:16:35,170 --> 01:16:37,270
MANY HAVE LONG SINCE
TURNED TO DUST.

986
01:16:37,300 --> 01:16:38,870
AND I SOBBED
AND I SOBBED.

987
01:16:38,910 --> 01:16:40,270
AND A YOUNG MAN STEPPED
OUT AND HE SAID,

988
01:16:40,310 --> 01:16:42,140
"WE'RE GOING DOWN
TO THE RESCUE MISSION.

989
01:16:42,180 --> 01:16:44,310
WON'T YOU COME
DOWN AND JOIN US?"

990
01:16:44,350 --> 01:16:45,510
I SAID,
"WHAT WILL I HEAR THERE?"

991
01:16:45,550 --> 01:16:48,750
HE SAID, "YOU'LL HEAR DRUNKARDS
TELL HOW THEY'VE BEEN SAVED.

992
01:16:48,780 --> 01:16:50,080
"YOU'LL HEAR GIRLS TELL
HOW THEY'VE BEEN SAVED

993
01:16:50,120 --> 01:16:52,020
IN THE RED LIGHT DISTRICT."

994
01:16:52,050 --> 01:16:55,090
WELL, I TURNED AND I SAID
TO THE BOYS, "WE'RE THROUGH.

995
01:16:55,120 --> 01:16:56,790
WE'VE COME TO THE PARTING
OF THE WAYS."

996
01:16:56,820 --> 01:16:58,090
AND I TURNED
MY BACK ON THEM.

997
01:16:58,130 --> 01:17:00,260
ONE OF THEM LAUGHED,
ONE OF THEM MOCKED ME,

998
01:17:00,290 --> 01:17:02,130
OTHERS NEVER
SAID A WORD.

999
01:17:02,160 --> 01:17:04,730
THIRTY-TWO YEARS AGO, I TURNED,
AND WENT DOWN TO THAT MISSION,

1000
01:17:04,770 --> 01:17:07,400
FELL ON MY KNEES AND
STAGGERED OUT OF MY SIN

1001
01:17:07,440 --> 01:17:10,140
AND INTO THE ARMS
OF THE SAVIOR.

1002
01:17:10,170 --> 01:17:14,040
SAY, HAVE YOU EVER BEEN WASHED
IN THE BLOOD OF THE LAMB OF GOD?

1003
01:17:14,070 --> 01:17:16,910
HAVE YOU EVER TURNED FROM
YOUR OWN SINFUL WAY OF LIVING

1004
01:17:16,940 --> 01:17:19,410
AND ASKED JESUS
TO SAVE YOUR SOUL?

1005
01:17:19,450 --> 01:17:21,050
I WONDER IF THERE
IS SOMEONE HERE TODAY

1006
01:17:21,080 --> 01:17:23,180
WHO WOULD ASK JESUS
TO SAVE HIM.

1007
01:17:23,220 --> 01:17:24,680
HE HAS MADE ALL THE
DIFFERENCE IN MY LIFE.

1008
01:17:24,720 --> 01:17:26,420
HE'LL DO
THE SAME FOR YOU.

1009
01:17:26,450 --> 01:17:30,020
JESUS SAID, "I AM THE WAY,
THE TRUTH, AND THE LIFE.

1010
01:17:30,060 --> 01:17:33,360
NO MAN COMETH UNTO
THE FATHER, BUT BY ME."

1011
01:17:33,390 --> 01:17:35,290
GOD HELP YOU
TO DO IT.

1012
01:17:35,330 --> 01:17:37,100
RODEY,
LET'S SING A SONG.

1013
01:17:42,050 --> 01:17:50,290
I'VE WANDERED FAR
AWAY FROM GOD.

1014
01:17:50,330 --> 01:17:57,300
NOW I'M COMIN' HOME.

1015
01:17:57,340 --> 01:18:05,310
THE PATHS OF SIN
TOO LONG I'VE TROD

1016
01:18:05,340 --> 01:18:12,780
NOW, I'M COMIN' HOME.

1017
01:18:12,820 --> 01:18:22,860
COMIN' HOME, COMIN' HOME,
NEVER MORE TO ROAM;

1018
01:18:22,860 --> 01:18:29,900
COMIN' HOME, COMIN' HOME,
NEVER MORE TO ROAM;

1019
01:18:29,930 --> 01:18:39,070
OPEN WIDE,
THINE ARMS OF LOVE

1020
01:18:39,110 --> 01:18:48,430
LORD, I'M COMING HOME.

1021
01:18:48,470 --> 01:18:57,240
KEEP YOUR EYES ON THE LORD.
W.A. SUNDAY.

1022
01:18:57,280 --> 01:18:58,240
THANK YOU,
SIR.

1023
01:18:58,280 --> 01:18:58,810
YOU'RE WELCOME.

1024
01:18:58,850 --> 01:18:59,450
NICE TO
MEET YOU.

1025
01:18:59,480 --> 01:19:02,780
YOU TOO.
GOD BLESS YOU.

1026
01:19:02,820 --> 01:19:05,080
MR. SUNDAY,
I WANT TO THANK YA.

1027
01:19:05,120 --> 01:19:07,420
YOU'RE WELCOME, SON.

1028
01:19:07,460 --> 01:19:09,320
EVERYTHING YA
SAID TONIGHT,

1029
01:19:09,360 --> 01:19:14,360
IT WAS LIKE YOU
WAS SPEAKIN' TO ME ALONE.

1030
01:19:14,400 --> 01:19:16,330
I GAVE MY HEART
TO CHRIST TONIGHT.

1031
01:19:16,360 --> 01:19:18,160
YOU'LL NEVER
BE SORRY, SON.

1032
01:19:18,200 --> 01:19:19,200
WHAT'S THE NAME?

1033
01:19:19,230 --> 01:19:20,300
CHARLES SPANGLER.

1034
01:19:20,330 --> 01:19:21,800
CHARLES.

1035
01:19:21,840 --> 01:19:25,900
I GREW UP
IN THE MILL.

1036
01:19:25,940 --> 01:19:28,170
MY DADDY
WAS BAD TO DRINK.

1037
01:19:28,210 --> 01:19:31,040
SO MY FOLKS NEVER TOLD
ME HOW TO BE SAVED.

1038
01:19:31,080 --> 01:19:33,850
GROWING UP IN A CHRISTIAN
HOME WON'T SAVE ANYONE.

1039
01:19:33,880 --> 01:19:35,810
MY OWN BOYS,

1040
01:19:35,850 --> 01:19:38,180
THEY HAVE THEIR STRUGGLES,
JUST LIKE EVERYONE ELSE.

1041
01:19:38,220 --> 01:19:40,320
EVERY SOUL MUST COME
TO CHRIST FOR HIMSELF.

1042
01:19:40,350 --> 01:19:42,220
IT'S NOT A
FAMILY DEAL.

1043
01:19:44,390 --> 01:19:47,890
HEY, UM, THIS HERE'S
MY FRIEND, WILL WRIGHT.

1044
01:19:47,930 --> 01:19:49,430
(MR. SUNDAY)
HELLO, WILL.

1045
01:19:49,460 --> 01:19:51,060
WE PLAY BASEBALL
FOR NEWTON MILL.

1046
01:19:51,100 --> 01:19:53,330
IS THAT RIGHT?

1047
01:19:53,370 --> 01:19:55,370
JOE JACKSON GOT HIS START
DOWN HERE, DIDN'T HE?

1048
01:19:55,400 --> 01:19:56,300
THAT'S RIGHT, SIR!

1049
01:19:56,340 --> 01:19:58,440
OH, IT'S A GREAT GAME.
I LOVED IT DEARLY.

1050
01:19:58,470 --> 01:19:59,370
BUT, AS I
SHARED TONIGHT,

1051
01:19:59,410 --> 01:20:02,040
I FOUND A HIGHER CALLING
WHEN I FOUND CHRIST.

1052
01:20:02,080 --> 01:20:04,340
THAT'S WHY YOU
LEFT BASEBALL?

1053
01:20:04,380 --> 01:20:07,950
WELL, I PLAYED FOR A FEW
YEARS AFTER I GOT SAVED,

1054
01:20:07,980 --> 01:20:09,920
BUT I FELT LIKE I WAS-

1055
01:20:09,950 --> 01:20:11,920
LIKE I WAS WEARIN'
SOMEONE ELSE'S SHOES.

1056
01:20:11,950 --> 01:20:13,320
I STILL LOVE THE GAME...

1057
01:20:13,350 --> 01:20:15,590
YOU ROUNDED THE BASES
IN 14 SECONDS.

1058
01:20:15,620 --> 01:20:17,520
AND NOW I ROUND THE PLATFORM
IN 2 HOURS.

1059
01:20:17,560 --> 01:20:19,090
[CHUCKLES]

1060
01:20:21,500 --> 01:20:23,060
YOU RECKON' YOU
COULD SIGN MY BIBLE?

1061
01:20:23,100 --> 01:20:24,500
SURE.

1062
01:20:31,210 --> 01:20:32,040
NICE TO MEET YOU.

1063
01:20:32,070 --> 01:20:32,500
THANK YOU, SIR.

1064
01:20:41,980 --> 01:20:44,480
CHICK, WE'RE SO GLAD
FOR YOUR DECISION!

1065
01:20:44,520 --> 01:20:47,850
THANK YOU
FER INVITIN' ME.

1066
01:20:47,890 --> 01:20:51,320
I'VE BEEN
PRAYIN' FOR YOU.

1067
01:20:51,360 --> 01:20:53,490
THANKS FOR THET -
IMOGENE.

1068
01:21:02,040 --> 01:21:05,100
HAVE YOU TALKED WITH HIM ABOUT
CHRIST BEFORE?

1069
01:21:05,140 --> 01:21:09,310
I DON'T RECOLLECT.
MAYBE I HAVE.

1070
01:21:09,340 --> 01:21:13,080
WILL - WHEN DID YOU
ASK CHRIST TO SAVE YOU?

1071
01:21:15,480 --> 01:21:16,650
WHEN I WAS
REAL LITTLE.

1072
01:21:16,680 --> 01:21:19,520
I CAN'T HARDLY
REMEMBER.

1073
01:21:19,550 --> 01:21:21,350
BUT YOU DO REMEMBER
IT HAPPENED?

1074
01:21:21,390 --> 01:21:24,960
YEAH, MY MA PRAYED
WITH ME.

1075
01:21:24,990 --> 01:21:27,060
MAY I SEE WHAT MR. SUNDAY
WROTE IN YOUR BIBLE?

1076
01:21:27,090 --> 01:21:28,090
SURE.

1077
01:21:30,500 --> 01:21:34,500
"TO WILL, KEEP YOUR EYES ON
THE LORD. W.A. SUNDAY."

1078
01:21:38,640 --> 01:21:42,210
SO, UM, EZEKIEL, WHAT DID
YOU THINK OF MR. SUNDAY?

1079
01:21:42,240 --> 01:21:45,610
WELL, I'M THANKFUL FOR HIS
STRONG STAND FOR RIGHT.

1080
01:21:45,650 --> 01:21:48,210
GRANTED THE WAY HE SLANGS
UP THE GOSPEL

1081
01:21:48,250 --> 01:21:50,480
IS A BIT UNDISTINGUISHED
FOR A PREACHER,

1082
01:21:50,520 --> 01:21:54,250
BUT HE DOES SEEM TO CONNECT
WITH THE COMMON MAN-

1083
01:21:54,290 --> 01:21:56,190
WELL, I DIDN'T EXPECT
TO SEE YOU HERE!

1084
01:21:56,220 --> 01:21:58,960
WILL!
OH, MY DEAR BOY.

1085
01:22:01,230 --> 01:22:04,360
LIKE I SAID,
SHE'S A HUGGER.

1086
01:22:04,400 --> 01:22:06,370
MA, I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET
A FRIEND OF MINE.

1087
01:22:06,400 --> 01:22:08,200
YES, DEAR.
OF COURSE.

1088
01:22:08,240 --> 01:22:09,470
THIS IS GINNIE DOUGLAS.

1089
01:22:09,500 --> 01:22:11,470
SHE'S A SECRETARY
DOWN AT THE MILL.

1090
01:22:11,510 --> 01:22:12,600
I'M PLEASED TO MEET YOU, MA'AM.

1091
01:22:12,640 --> 01:22:14,210
AND I YOU,
GINNIE.

1092
01:22:14,240 --> 01:22:15,370
HOW DO
YOU DO?

1093
01:22:15,410 --> 01:22:16,940
I KNOW
THE YOUNG LADY.

1094
01:22:16,980 --> 01:22:18,340
HOW ARE YOU,
VIRGINIA?

1095
01:22:18,380 --> 01:22:20,010
I'M DOIN' FINE,
MR. HAMPTON.

1096
01:22:20,050 --> 01:22:21,150
IS YOUR
FATHER HERE?

1097
01:22:21,180 --> 01:22:23,620
YES, HE'S OUTSIDE GATHERING UP
THE BOYS IN THE TRUCK.

1098
01:22:23,650 --> 01:22:26,250
UH, VIRGINIA'S
FATHER IS RESPONSIBLE

1099
01:22:26,290 --> 01:22:29,090
FOR THE BOY'S RECREATION
DOWN AT THE MILL.

1100
01:22:29,120 --> 01:22:31,490
IN FACT, IF YOU
WOULD EXCUSE ME,

1101
01:22:31,530 --> 01:22:34,260
I'D LIKE TO GO THANK HIM FOR
BRINGING A GROUP OUT TONIGHT.

1102
01:22:34,300 --> 01:22:36,090
LADIES.

1103
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:46,340
MR. HAMPTON TELLS ME YOU'RE AN
APPRENTICE MACHINIST, WILLIAM.

1104
01:22:46,370 --> 01:22:48,140
WELL HE'S JUST
PUTTING IT KINDLY.

1105
01:22:48,180 --> 01:22:50,410
I JUST LOOK
AFTER THE LOOMS

1106
01:22:50,440 --> 01:22:51,610
AND THEN IF SOMETHING
GOES WRONG THEN,

1107
01:22:51,650 --> 01:22:55,110
I GO AND GET
REAL HELP.

1108
01:22:55,150 --> 01:22:57,220
WILL'S TOLD ME
ALL ABOUT YA.

1109
01:22:57,250 --> 01:22:58,620
GOOD THINGS,
I HOPE?

1110
01:22:58,650 --> 01:22:59,850
YES.

1111
01:22:59,890 --> 01:23:03,150
I'M SO PLEASED TO HEAR ABOUT THE
PROMISE YOU ASKED HIM TO KEEP.

1112
01:23:03,190 --> 01:23:05,090
HE TOLD YOU?

1113
01:23:05,130 --> 01:23:07,630
WELL,
I'M GLAD HE DID.

1114
01:23:07,660 --> 01:23:09,030
(MA)
WILL?

1115
01:23:09,060 --> 01:23:10,760
YES, MA?

1116
01:23:10,800 --> 01:23:12,530
I'M THANKFUL THAT YOU HAVEN'T
FORGOTTEN THE PROMISE

1117
01:23:12,570 --> 01:23:16,070
THAT YOU MADE TO ME THE NIGHT
YOU LEFT HOME.

1118
01:23:16,100 --> 01:23:20,110
CAN YOU LOOK ME IN THE EYE
AND TELL ME YOU'VE KEPT IT?

1119
01:23:20,140 --> 01:23:21,740
MA, THIS IS HARDLY
THE TIME OR PLACE

1120
01:23:21,780 --> 01:23:23,780
TO BE TALKING ABOUT
PERSONAL MATTERS.

1121
01:23:23,810 --> 01:23:25,540
WHAT IS THERE
TO TALK ABOUT?

1122
01:23:25,580 --> 01:23:27,650
OKAY,
I TRIED IT.

1123
01:23:27,680 --> 01:23:29,410
BUT I HATED IT.

1124
01:23:29,450 --> 01:23:30,620
I JUST PROMISED MY PAL
THE OTHER DAY

1125
01:23:30,650 --> 01:23:33,620
THAT I WOULD NOT EVEN
TOUCH ANOTHER DROP.

1126
01:23:33,650 --> 01:23:36,620
WILL,
I'M DISAPPOINTED.

1127
01:23:36,660 --> 01:23:42,360
IT'S OKAY, MA,
I'M DONE FOR GOOD.

1128
01:23:42,400 --> 01:23:46,270
WILL, WILL YOU COME
HOME FOR A VISIT?

1129
01:23:46,300 --> 01:23:50,700
I CAN'T, MA.
I'M SORRY.

1130
01:23:50,740 --> 01:23:54,640
I'M A JUST A BIT TIED UP
TONIGHT.

1131
01:23:54,680 --> 01:23:57,480
PA, YOU'LL BE GLAD TO KNOW
I'M HITTING WELL.

1132
01:23:57,510 --> 01:23:59,340
I MIGHT MAKE IT
OUT OF THE MILL.

1133
01:23:59,380 --> 01:24:01,380
IS THAT RIGHT?

1134
01:24:03,420 --> 01:24:05,350
WELL, IF NOT TONIGHT,

1135
01:24:05,390 --> 01:24:10,360
MAYBE SOME SUNDAY YOU CAN MAKE
IT HOME AND BRING YOUR FRIENDS.

1136
01:24:10,390 --> 01:24:13,360
I'LL SEE IF I CAN MAKE
THAT WORK, MA.

1137
01:24:13,390 --> 01:24:15,530
WE'D BETTER GO.

1138
01:24:26,140 --> 01:24:28,510
SO ANYWAY, PEP,
THIS MR. SUNDAY

1139
01:24:28,540 --> 01:24:31,840
HE DELIVERS HIS SERMONS
LIKE A MAN ON FIRE.

1140
01:24:31,880 --> 01:24:36,150
SAYS IT DON'T MATTER
HOW RICH YA ARE-

1141
01:24:36,180 --> 01:24:40,220
OR HOW SMART YA ARE-

1142
01:24:40,250 --> 01:24:41,690
OR EVEN HOW FAMOUS.

1143
01:24:41,720 --> 01:24:44,790
EVEN IF YOU MAKE THE HALL OF
FAME- IT AIN'T GOOD ENOUGH.

1144
01:24:48,400 --> 01:24:51,400
YOU GOTTA PUT YER
FAITH IN CHRIST ALONE.

1145
01:24:54,540 --> 01:24:58,100
OH, SPANGLER,
ARE YOU PREACHIN' OR PITCHIN'?

1146
01:24:58,140 --> 01:24:59,270
I'M PITCHIN'.

1147
01:24:59,310 --> 01:25:02,410
THEN SHUT UP
AND PITCH.

1148
01:25:02,440 --> 01:25:06,510
'TWEEN YOUR FOOL PREACHIN' AND
YOUR BROTHER'S FOOL SNAKE BITE,

1149
01:25:06,550 --> 01:25:09,650
WE'RE THE WORSE OFF
FOR THE BOTH A' YA.

1150
01:25:09,680 --> 01:25:14,250
AND AS FOR YOU, WRIGHT, YOU
LOOK LIKE YOU'RE SLEEP WALKIN'.

1151
01:25:14,290 --> 01:25:16,290
LET'S SEE SOME
PEP OUT THERE.

1152
01:25:36,910 --> 01:25:41,110
[MUSIC]

1153
01:25:51,290 --> 01:25:53,790
READY TO GO?

1154
01:25:53,830 --> 01:25:57,300
I...I GOTTA GET SOMETHING
TO DRINK.

1155
01:25:57,330 --> 01:25:58,930
I THOUGHT YA'S
ON TH' WAGON.

1156
01:25:58,970 --> 01:26:02,770
YEAH, I JUST,
I DON'T KNOW.

1157
01:26:02,800 --> 01:26:04,800
I JUST DON'T
FEEL LIKE MYSELF.

1158
01:26:08,210 --> 01:26:11,240
WILL, YOU BETTER
STAY AWAY FROM IT.

1159
01:26:11,280 --> 01:26:13,310
LOOK, I'M GLAD YOU'RE A
CHRISTIAN NOW AND EVERYTHING,

1160
01:26:13,350 --> 01:26:15,250
BUT JUST CUT IT OUT,
DOGGONE IT!!!

1161
