HE HERE?

1614
01:55:07,380 --> 01:55:10,050
EVEN IF HE DOES SHOW, THERE
AIN'T NO WAY I'LL PUT HIM IN.

1615
01:55:10,080 --> 01:55:13,320
HE'D ONLY FOUL
THINGS UP.

1616
01:55:13,350 --> 01:55:15,190
NEVER SEEN A FOOL BALL
PLAYER LATE TO THE BIGGEST,

1617
01:55:15,220 --> 01:55:17,220
DOGGONE BALL GAME
OF THE YEAR!

1618
01:55:20,230 --> 01:55:27,230
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

1619
01:55:27,270 --> 01:55:30,070
WELCOME TO THE
CHAMPIONSHIP GAME,

1620
01:55:30,100 --> 01:55:32,270
WHICH BRINGS THE
ANDERSON TEAM TO NEWTON MILL

1621
01:55:32,300 --> 01:55:35,340
FOR THE LAST GAME OF THE SEASON.

1622
01:55:35,370 --> 01:55:37,140
(UMPIRE)
PLAY BALL!

1623
01:55:37,180 --> 01:55:47,580
[CHEERING]

1624
01:55:57,260 --> 01:56:02,330
NOW YOUNG MAN, I WANT YOU
TO BE JUST AS STILL AS YOU CAN.

1625
01:56:02,370 --> 01:56:07,070
I DON'T WANT
NO MORE NEEDLES!

1626
01:56:07,110 --> 01:56:10,540
WE'RE GIVIN' HIM SOMETHING
TO SETTLE HIM DOWN.

1627
01:56:10,580 --> 01:56:13,480
HE'LL BE ALRIGHT.

1628
01:56:13,510 --> 01:56:16,350
IT'S OKAY, BO.

1629
01:56:16,380 --> 01:56:17,610
THE DOCTOR'S JUST DOIN'
WHAT HE'S GOT TO DO

1630
01:56:17,650 --> 01:56:19,980
TO MAKE SURE
YOU'RE OKAY.

1631
01:56:20,020 --> 01:56:21,550
I'M HERE WITH YOU,
BUDDY.

1632
01:56:21,590 --> 01:56:24,090
WILL, YOU GOTTA GET
TO THE GAME!

1633
01:56:24,120 --> 01:56:25,620
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THE GAME.

1634
01:56:25,660 --> 01:56:28,220
IT'S MORE IMPORTANT
THAT I SEE YOU'RE OKAY.

1635
01:56:28,260 --> 01:56:30,360
WILL, PLEASE GO.

1636
01:56:30,400 --> 01:56:32,130
IT'S OKAY, BO.

1637
01:56:32,160 --> 01:56:36,030
JUST TAKE IT EASY.
IT'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY.

1638
01:56:43,040 --> 01:56:45,140
(ANNOUNCER) TWO OUTS IN THE TOP
OF THE SECOND.

1639
01:56:45,180 --> 01:56:48,340
SPANGLER'S TRYIN'
TO GET THAT LAST STRIKE.

1640
01:56:48,380 --> 01:56:50,980
COME ON, SPANGLER!
STRIKE HIM OUT.

1641
01:56:59,160 --> 01:57:00,690
YOU'RE OUT!

1642
01:57:02,330 --> 01:57:06,560
[CHEERING]

1643
01:57:11,400 --> 01:57:15,740
CHICK, I'M WORRIED
ABOUT WILL.

1644
01:57:15,770 --> 01:57:18,510
YEAH, I'M WONDERING
WHERE PIKE IS.

1645
01:57:28,650 --> 01:57:30,690
HE'LL SLEEP
A LONG TIME NOW.

1646
01:57:30,720 --> 01:57:31,760
YOU CAN GO.

1647
01:57:31,790 --> 01:57:34,790
YOU SURE DOC?
THANK YA.

1648
01:57:45,140 --> 01:57:46,440
SORRY.

1649
01:57:51,840 --> 01:57:55,040
[MUSIC]

1650
01:58:08,690 --> 01:58:10,230
UGH, PIKE!

1651
01:58:10,260 --> 01:58:13,260
[MUSIC]

1652
01:58:39,390 --> 01:58:41,420
(ANNOUNCER) THAT'S THE LAST OUT
FOR ANDERSON.

1653
01:58:41,460 --> 01:58:43,390
WE GO TO THE BOTTOM
OF THE FIFTH.

1654
01:58:43,430 --> 01:58:46,660
I DON'T SEE
WILL ANYWHERE.

1655
01:58:46,700 --> 01:58:48,900
IT'S NOT LIKE HIM
TO MISS A GAME.

1656
01:58:48,930 --> 01:58:50,770
I HOPE THERE'S
NO TROUBLE.

1657
01:58:50,800 --> 01:58:52,840
HE'S PROBABLY ON
HIS WAY RIGHT NOW.

1658
01:58:54,410 --> 01:58:55,810
(ANNOUNCER) WE'RE HALF WAY
THROUGH THE GAME.

1659
01:58:55,840 --> 01:58:59,410
NEWTON HAS A MAN ON SECOND,
BUT THEY NEED TO GET HIM HOME.

1660
01:59:05,420 --> 01:59:07,480
COME ON, HUNNICUTT.
GET ON BASE!

1661
01:59:11,760 --> 01:59:20,900
[CHEERING]

1662
01:59:20,930 --> 01:59:21,830
OUT!

1663
01:59:21,870 --> 01:59:23,270
[DISAPPOINTED MOANS]

1664
01:59:24,670 --> 01:59:26,370
SAFE.

1665
01:59:26,400 --> 01:59:34,910
[CHEERING]

1666
01:59:34,950 --> 01:59:37,410
(COACH) ON THE BALL NOW;
KEEP YOUR EYE ON THE BALL.

1667
01:59:45,720 --> 01:59:47,390
SAFE!

1668
01:59:47,430 --> 01:59:56,330
[CHEERING]

1669
02:00:00,970 --> 02:00:04,190
[MUSIC]

1670
02:00:34,320 --> 02:00:36,320
'SPECTED YOU
A LONG TIME AGO.

1671
02:00:36,360 --> 02:00:37,860
I FIGURED AS MUCH.

1672
02:00:40,930 --> 02:00:44,530
GOT SOME UNFINISHED
BUSINESS WITH YOU TOWN BOY.

1673
02:00:44,570 --> 02:00:47,930
I GOTTA GIT TO
THE GAME, PIKE.

1674
02:00:47,970 --> 02:00:56,610
NO... SEE, THAT'S
THE WHOLE POINT,

1675
02:00:56,650 --> 02:00:58,410
YOU AIN'T GOTTA
GO NOWHERE.

1676
02:00:58,450 --> 02:00:59,880
CLEAR OUTTA
MY WAY.

1677
02:00:59,920 --> 02:01:02,280
I THINK WE'RE
GOOD RIGHT HERE.

1678
02:01:02,320 --> 02:01:03,420
I'M COMIN' THROUGH,
PIKE.

1679
02:01:03,450 --> 02:01:04,680
YA THINK SO?

1680
02:01:04,720 --> 02:01:06,550
GET OUT OF
MY WAY.

1681
02:01:06,590 --> 02:01:08,960
HOW DO YOU
THINK IT FELT

1682
02:01:08,990 --> 02:01:12,930
WHEN THET BALL YA THREW
HIT BO IN THE HEAD?

1683
02:01:15,760 --> 02:01:17,730
I DON'T KNOW.

1684
02:01:17,770 --> 02:01:19,730
MUST 'A' HURT
SOMETHIN' AWFUL.

1685
02:01:22,000 --> 02:01:23,440
YOU'RE CRAZY!

1686
02:01:23,470 --> 02:01:24,870
AND YOU'RE DEAD.

1687
02:01:50,730 --> 02:01:53,870
I AIN'T GONNA THANK YA IF
THETS WHAT YER WAITIN' FER.

1688
02:01:53,900 --> 02:01:57,970
IF YOU EVER KNEW WHAT IT
FELT LIKE TO BE SET FREE -

1689
02:01:58,010 --> 02:02:02,380
I DON'T KNOW, YOU MIGHT BE
A DIFFERENT PERSON.

1690
02:02:02,410 --> 02:02:03,880
MAYBE ONE DAY.

1691
02:02:11,020 --> 02:02:20,960
[MUSIC]

1692
02:02:21,000 --> 02:02:23,130
THERE HE IS,
THERE'S WILL.

1693
02:02:23,160 --> 02:02:32,100
[MUSIC]

1694
02:02:32,140 --> 02:02:33,270
WHO DO YOU
THINK YOU ARE?

1695
02:02:33,310 --> 02:02:36,840
YOU THINK YOU CAN JUST WALTZ
IN HERE ANYTIME YOU WANT?

1696
02:02:36,880 --> 02:02:39,380
SIT DOWN AND KEEP
YER TRAP SHUT!

1697
02:02:47,760 --> 02:02:48,890
IS THAT SCOUT
FROM CHARLOTTE HERE?

1698
02:02:48,920 --> 02:02:52,490
YEAH, HE'S HERE.

1699
02:02:52,530 --> 02:02:54,890
HE AIN'T SEEIN'
MUCH FROM US THOUGH.

1700
02:02:58,070 --> 02:03:00,570
WILL, YA WANT ME TO TALK
TO SCOOP FER YA?

1701
02:03:00,600 --> 02:03:02,970
NO.

1702
02:03:03,000 --> 02:03:05,140
I MISSED THE FIRST SEVEN INNINGS
OF THE CHAMPIONSHIP GAME.

1703
02:03:05,170 --> 02:03:07,640
WHAT ELSE
CAN HE DO?

1704
02:03:13,480 --> 02:03:22,120
[CHEERING]

1705
02:03:22,160 --> 02:03:23,420
(UMPIRE) SAFE!

1706
02:03:27,630 --> 02:03:29,030
(ANNOUNCER)
LOOKS LIKE WILSON'S HURT.

1707
02:03:32,000 --> 02:03:34,770
WRIGHT, YOU'RE ALL I GOT,
GO IN AND RUN FOR HIM.

1708
02:03:34,800 --> 02:03:36,470
OKAY, COACH.

1709
02:03:38,140 --> 02:03:39,840
(ANNOUNCER) HERE COMES
WILL WRIGHT INTO THE GAME

1710
02:03:39,870 --> 02:03:41,010
TO RUN FOR WILSON.

1711
02:03:41,040 --> 02:03:53,720
[CLAPPING]

1712
02:03:53,760 --> 02:03:55,620
AT LEAST HE
WON'T GET TO BAT.

1713
02:03:55,660 --> 02:03:57,120
[WACK!]

1714
02:03:57,160 --> 02:04:02,000
[CHEERING]

1715
02:04:02,030 --> 02:04:03,900
THAT'S THE THIRD OUT.

1716
02:04:03,930 --> 02:04:06,130
NEWTON'S STILL BEHIND
BY TWO RUNS

1717
02:04:06,170 --> 02:04:08,030
AND WE'RE DOWN
TO THE LAST INNING.

1718
02:04:08,070 --> 02:04:20,180
[MUSIC]

1719
02:04:21,520 --> 02:04:22,850
(ANNOUNCER)
TWO OUTS FOR ANDERSON.

1720
02:04:22,880 --> 02:04:24,580
SPANGLER NEEDS
ONE MORE STRIKE

1721
02:04:24,620 --> 02:04:27,590
TO BRING THIS TEAM UP FOR
THEIR LAST CHANCE AT BAT.

1722
02:04:27,620 --> 02:04:34,530
[CHEERING]

1723
02:04:37,800 --> 02:04:45,070
[CHEERING]

1724
02:05:02,560 --> 02:05:03,290
[WACK!]

1725
02:05:03,320 --> 02:05:06,830
[CHEERING]

1726
02:05:12,300 --> 02:05:13,200
[WACK!]

1727
02:05:37,630 --> 02:05:38,690
[WACK!]

1728
02:05:42,630 --> 02:05:43,760
SAFE!

1729
02:05:52,210 --> 02:05:53,240
[WACK!]

1730
02:06:08,920 --> 02:06:11,290
WELL, WRIGHT, NO ONE
I'D RATHER HAVE COMIN'

1731
02:06:11,330 --> 02:06:13,560
TO THE PLATE RIGHT NOW.

1732
02:06:16,970 --> 02:06:18,260
Y'AIN'T BEEN
DRINKIN'?

1733
02:06:18,300 --> 02:06:20,930
NO, SIR.

1734
02:06:20,970 --> 02:06:25,170
OKAY, THEN,
MAKE US PROUD.

1735
02:06:28,040 --> 02:06:36,780
[CHEERING]

1736
02:06:45,260 --> 02:06:46,330
(UMPIRE) BALL.

1737
02:06:54,070 --> 02:06:55,870
GO WILL!

1738
02:07:09,980 --> 02:07:10,950
[WACK!]

1739
02:07:10,990 --> 02:07:25,900
[CHEERING]

1740
02:07:25,930 --> 02:07:26,830
GO, GO!

1741
02:07:33,980 --> 02:07:35,740
NO, NO!

1742
02:07:42,220 --> 02:07:43,750
SAFE!

1743
02:07:43,780 --> 02:07:45,950
[CHEERING]

1744
02:07:45,990 --> 02:07:48,150
OH, YAY, YOU DID IT!

1745
02:07:48,190 --> 02:07:58,060
[CHEERING]

1746
02:08:05,470 --> 02:08:08,840
MR. WRIGHT,
MR. WRIGHT.

1747
02:08:08,880 --> 02:08:09,940
CAN I SPEAK WITH YOU
FOR A MOMENT?

1748
02:08:28,800 --> 02:08:30,960
THANK YOU.

1749
02:08:41,080 --> 02:08:42,980
I OWE YOU A DEBT OF GRATITUDE,
MR. DOUGLAS.

1750
02:08:43,010 --> 02:08:45,040
THIS IS A CONTRACT FROM
THE CHARLOTTE SPINNERS!

1751
02:08:45,080 --> 02:08:47,850
I KNEW IT, I KNEW
YOU COULD DO IT.

1752
02:08:48,950 --> 02:08:51,780
IT'S WHAT YOU
ALWAYS DREAMED OF!

1753
02:08:51,820 --> 02:08:54,320
YOU DID NEWTON MILL PROUD,
WILL!

1754
02:08:54,360 --> 02:08:55,990
WILL, I CAN'T
BELIEVE IT!

1755
02:08:56,020 --> 02:08:57,920
I KNEW YA HAD IT
IN YA, TOWN BOY.

1756
02:08:57,960 --> 02:08:59,330
COULDNA DONE IT
WITHOUT YOU.

1757
02:08:59,360 --> 02:09:01,460
AIN'T GONNA BE TH'
SAME 'ROUND HERE.

1758
02:09:01,500 --> 02:09:03,200
YOU CAN'T GET RID
OF ME THAT FAST.

1759
02:09:03,230 --> 02:09:04,830
JOHN AND I CAME UP
WITH A PLAN.

1760
02:09:04,870 --> 02:09:05,970
IF I DO WELL
IN CHARLOTTE,

1761
02:09:06,000 --> 02:09:08,070
I CAN COME BACK IN THE
OFF-SEASON TO THE MILL. RIGHT?

1762
02:09:08,100 --> 02:09:09,940
THE OFFER'S
ALWAYS OPEN.

1763
02:09:09,970 --> 02:09:10,740
I WANT TO START
HELPIN' JOHN

1764
02:09:10,770 --> 02:09:12,840
WITH THE BOYS'
RECREATION LEAGUE.

1765
02:09:12,870 --> 02:09:15,940
I KNOW I CAN
USE SOME HELP!

1766
02:09:15,980 --> 02:09:20,780
AND, WELL, WHO KNOWS
WHAT THE FUTURE BRINGS!

1767
02:09:20,820 --> 02:09:22,350
(MA)
WILL!

1768
02:09:22,380 --> 02:09:25,320
MA?

1769
02:09:25,350 --> 02:09:27,490
SO PROUD OF YOU,
SON!

1770
02:09:30,260 --> 02:09:31,790
HOW IN THE WORLD
DID YOU -?

1771
02:09:31,830 --> 02:09:33,990
YOUR FRIEND TOLD US
ABOUT THE CHAMPIONSHIP.

1772
02:09:34,030 --> 02:09:36,500
SHE EVEN OFFERED TO COME
AND DRIVE US FROM TOWN.

1773
02:09:40,370 --> 02:09:46,340
MA, PA,
I'VE WRONGED YOU BOTH.

1774
02:09:46,370 --> 02:09:48,840
I'M SORRY.

1775
02:09:48,880 --> 02:09:51,040
WE CAN TALK ABOUT
THAT LATER, WILL.

1776
02:09:51,080 --> 02:09:52,880
WE FREELY
FORGIVE YOU.

1777
02:10:01,260 --> 02:10:03,260
LIKE I SAID -
SHE'S A HUGGER.

1778
02:10:05,360 --> 02:10:08,590
WILL, YOU'VE MADE SUCH WONDERFUL
FRIENDS WHILE YOU'VE BEEN AWAY!

1779
02:10:08,630 --> 02:10:12,060
GINNIE, THANK YOU
SO MUCH FOR TODAY!

1780
02:10:12,100 --> 02:10:13,930
I KNEW YOU'D
WANT TO BE HERE.

1781
02:10:13,970 --> 02:10:18,940
WILLIAM, I HAVE TO SAY I'VE BEEN
A BIT NARROW IN MY PERSPECTIVE

1782
02:10:18,970 --> 02:10:22,480
ON WHAT YOU COULD DO
WITH YOUR LIFE.

1783
02:10:22,510 --> 02:10:23,980
I'VE BEEN A BIT NARROW
IN MY PERSPECTIVE

1784
02:10:24,010 --> 02:10:26,580
ABOUT A GOOD
MANY THINGS.

1785
02:10:26,610 --> 02:10:29,520
BUT I AIM
TO DO BETTER.

1786
02:10:29,550 --> 02:10:31,850
THERE ARE NO STAINS ON
THE PAGES OF TOMORROW.

1787
02:10:31,890 --> 02:10:34,920
THAT'S RIGHT, SON.
THERE AREN'T.

1788
02:10:34,960 --> 02:10:38,860
WELL, IN THAT CASE, I HAVE
JUST ONE QUESTION FOR YOU.

1789
02:10:38,890 --> 02:10:40,060
WOULD IT BE ALRIGHT IF
I BROUGHT A MILL GIRL

1790
02:10:40,090 --> 02:10:42,460
TO MEET THE TOWN FOLK
AT CHURCH TOMORROW?

1791
02:10:42,500 --> 02:10:45,200
IF YOU DON'T BRING HER,
SON, I WILL.

1792
02:10:45,230 --> 02:10:47,330
SHE'S A KEEPER!

1793
02:10:47,370 --> 02:10:50,240
WELL, YOU READY?
